This will test FAMILY's ability to play sound through headphones.
<!-- Smells: UNVERIFIED STEPS, PRE CONDITION AS STEP -->
<dl>
    <dt>Ensure that the sound volume is turned to a reasonable level and that the sound is not muted by clicking on the Volume Control applet (the speaker icon in the notification area) and setting the volume</dt>
    <dt>Select home folder on the unity panel</dt>
    <dt>Open the Examples folder, Open the Ubuntu_Free_Culture_Showcase folder</dt>
    <dt>Select either of the .ogg files</dt>
        <dd>The file opens in your default media player</dd>
    <dd>Sound should be played through the headphones without strange noises or distortions</dd>
    <dt>Adjust the volume with the Volume Control applet. Verify that the audio volume changes</dt>
    <dt>Right-click the Volume Control icon and check Mute</dt>
        <dd>The volume is muted</dd>
    <dt>Right-click the Volume Control icon and uncheck Mute</dt>
        <dd>Audio resumes</dd>
</dl>

